baseball/33.txt::0.text: What is your favorite play in baseball?

baseball/33.txt::1.text: Ooh, that's a tie between a "little-league homerun" and an "inside the park homerun".

baseball/33.txt::10.text: I saw that the other day! It's hilarious.

baseball/33.txt::11.text: So what's more exciting, the inside-the-parker or the little-leaguer?

baseball/33.txt::12.text: I like the inside-the-park, because it's less on human error, minus a judgement call, and more about a massive sprint.

baseball/33.txt::13.text: It's especially funny when the batter is fat.

baseball/33.txt::14.text: Yeah, an easy inside-the-park homerun would be barely a triple for Frank Thomas. If not, an out.

baseball/33.txt::17.text: Let's say two outfielders are both going to the ball, but collide and are both knocked out. Is it an error or a hit?

baseball/33.txt::18.text: No idea, but I'd pay good money to watch that. That seems hilarious.

baseball/33.txt::19.text: Yeah, even more so if the third outfielder runs up to get the ball, and trips over them. Just a series of injuries.

baseball/33.txt::3.text: Well, these are all highly-paid super athletes. Yet these two situations rely on gross incompetence.

baseball/33.txt::5.text: Well, the little-league home run is based entirely on errors. It's usually a bases-loaded situation and the team just over throws or misses their targets, letting everyone continue to run.

baseball/33.txt::6.text: So, it's not a home run, then.

baseball/33.txt::8.text: It's a series of errors, not a home run.

baseball/33.txt::9.text: You know what I mean. But the best part is a little-league grand slam.

star_wars/12.txt::4.text: I was thinking that exactly the same. In the Attack of the Clones, Annakin jumps out of a vehicle and falls thousands of feet.

star_wars/12.txt::5.text: Yes that's a great point. My only thought is that Palpatine must have ignited an explosion.

star_wars/12.txt::6.text: Oh right, because there is that huge blue fireball that comes back up the shaft.

star_wars/12.txt::7.text: Yes, so that is my thought: that he must have hit some fuel cell with his force lightning which ignited a huge explosion.

star_wars/12.txt::8.text: Great thanks! I was wondering why he couldn't survive a "little" fall like that.

star_wars/12.txt::9.text: No worries. That seems to be the best explanation that I can think of.

star_wars/13.txt::0.text: Which Star Wars movie do you like the most?

star_wars/13.txt::1.text: For me, it's Empire Strikes Back, because when I was a kid the wait to see what happened next was so long and exciting!

star_wars/13.txt::2.text: You don't find that Empire seems outdated compared to today's movie standards?

star_wars/13.txt::3.text: Well, you can't compare older movies' effects to today's CGI stuff, which is why George Lucas went back and tried to digitally edit new CGI in.

star_wars/13.txt::4.text: That didn't go too well, since it made the new graphics in all of those original trilogy movies stick out like a sore thumb.

star_wars/13.txt::5.text: Sure, but you'll note that Empire Strikes Back had the least amount of new scenes added for the Special Edition.

star_wars/13.txt::6.text: That probably means Empire Strikes Back was probably good enough to stand the test of time.

star_wars/13.txt::7.text: Exactly what I was saying, and that's one of the main reason why I think Empire Strikes Back is my favorite!

star_wars/13.txt::8.text: Well, I thought Jar Jar was funny in the Phantom Menace.

star_wars/13.txt::9.text: I don't know where you get your delusions, laser brain" - That's a line from Empire Strikes back and fitting to what you just told me.

star_wars/20.txt::0.text: Disney has been doing a great job on making movies these days, especially the Star Wars movies.

star_wars/20.txt::1.text: I agree. The Force Awakens was a surprise to me in how good it was. I think Disney was wise to hire JJ. Abrams to direct the movie.

star_wars/20.txt::2.text: I think with a foundation as huge as Star Wars and 245 Million budget, JJ. Abrams could not go wrong.

star_wars/20.txt::3.text: Correct. Do you think that the Last Jedi will be as great?

star_wars/20.txt::4.text: I plan on it being so. I'm really hoping that Luky Skywalker plays more of a part in the Last Jedi then the little bits and pieces he had in the Force Awakens.

star_wars/20.txt::5.text: I would think we will see more of Mark Hamill, because I believe his character Luke is the Last Jedi.

star_wars/20.txt::6.text: What about Carrie Fischer and her Leia character?

star_wars/20.txt::7.text: God rest her soul, but I am hoping to see JJ. Abrams and Disney incorporate Princess Leia into the Last Jedi.

star_wars/20.txt::8.text: I think many of her fans are hoping and praying for that as well.

star_wars/20.txt::9.text: We can only wait and see what the future holds in store for The Last Jedi.

star_wars/9.txt::0.text: What did you like most about Star Wars movies?

star_wars/9.txt::1.text: I've seen them all and I think I like the story of young Anakin the most.

star_wars/9.txt::2.text: That's from Star Wars Episode I right?

star_wars/9.txt::3.text: Yes.  It's the fourth movie but the beginning of the series as a whole.

star_wars/9.txt::4.text: I remember, that's the movie with the speed pod racing.

star_wars/9.txt::5.text: Right.  And Anakin is the pilot of the winning pod, but I just like seeing him when he's young before he becomes Darth Vader.

star_wars/9.txt::6.text: I never thought of it like that.  Darth Vader was certainly a very menacing person.

star_wars/9.txt::7.text: I agree, that's why it was nice to see him as a young and innocent child.

star_wars/9.txt::8.text: Looking back, it didn't take long for him to lose that innocence either.  By Episode II he was already showing his dark side.

star_wars/9.txt::9.text: Definitely.  You can already see the Darth Vader in him by that point.
